{"parentUuid":"b6308ea3-aa7c-4b51-9f38-8e3e522519fc","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"3cfdca64-d5a0-407a-b98d-81d58c820453","agentId":"a98d53b8f2a71429f","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01HoRNp2W9FRzGNgWxi3qYh9","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"how movements scale digitally open source Wikipedia Khan Academy network effects mission-driven\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Social Movements | Society and Culture | MCAT | Khan Academy | Digital Citizenship+ Resource Platform\",\"url\":\"https://dcrp.berkman.harvard.edu/external-resource/social-movements-society-and-culture-mcat-khan-academy-7\"},{\"title\":\"Khan's Biggest Impact: Changing the Economics of Education - Big Think\",\"url\":\"http://bigthink.com/disrupt-education/khans-biggest-impact-changing-the-economics-of-education\"},{\"title\":\"(PDF) Open Source Movements as a Model for Organizing.\",\"url\":\"https://www.researchgate.net/publication/221408272_Open_Source_Movements_as_a_Model_for_Organizing\"},{\"title\":\"Khan Academy\",\"url\":\"https://www.khanacademy.org/about\"},{\"title\":\"Open Source – Khan Academy\",\"url\":\"https://khan.github.io/\"},{\"title\":\"The Role of Purpose & Vision in Building Movements with Sal Khan - Mayfield\",\"url\":\"https://www.mayfield.com/the-role-of-purpose-vision-in-building-movements-with-sal-khan/\"},{\"title\":\"Khan Academy and Stand Together Trust Announce Partnership to Leverage AI to Transform Education\",\"url\":\"https://standtogether.org/newsroom/education/khan-academy-and-stand-together-trust-partner-on-education\"},{\"title\":\"Hacking computer science education at Khan Academy | Opensource.com\",\"url\":\"https://opensource.com/education/14/2/computer-science-khan-academy\"},{\"title\":\"Is there an open source Khan Academy platform? - Quora\",\"url\":\"https://www.quora.com/Is-there-an-open-source-Khan-Academy-platform\"},{\"title\":\"Read \\\"How People Learn II: Learners, Contexts, and Cultures\\\" at NAP.edu\",\"url\":\"https://www.nationalacademies.org/read/24783/chapter/10\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's what I found about how movements scale digitally with open source, Wikipedia, Khan Academy, network effects, and mission-driven approaches:\n\n## Mission-Driven Scaling Through Digital Platforms\n\nKhan Academy founder Sal Khan left a successful career on Wall Street to embark on a mission to provide free world class education for anyone, anywhere on the planet. Khan Academy's mission as a not-for-profit is providing free world class education for anyone, anywhere. Worldwide, more than 160 million registered learners have used Khan Academy in 190 countries and more than 50 languages.\n\n## Non-Commercial Open Source Model\n\nKhan and Wikipedia's Jimmy Wales are proving that there is \"a better way\" to deliver true free education on the Internet. Khan Academy has always been ad-free although Khan could make significant income based on either Google Ads or by selling sponsorships based on his reach, yet Khan Academy stays a noncommercial platform. Most Khan Academy content is released under a Creative Commons license.\n\n## Network Effects and Scalability\n\nKhan Schools Network, established in 2023, aims to develop and share open source mastery-based educational resources, including curriculum, instructional materials, and a school design playbook. The organization works to actively engage in research and development endeavors, particularly those with scalable goals, in collaboration with partners.\n\n## Open Source Project Leadership\n\nResearch on open source movements shows that while OSS projects lack formal organizational structure, project leaders play a significant role in initiating and managing these projects and eventually influencing the degree to which the developed software is used and liked by users.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"ea4cbd54-a50c-4305-accd-ebad8fea0dc1","timestamp":"2026-03-15T14:18:51.508Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"b6308ea3-aa7c-4b51-9f38-8e3e522519fc","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
