{"parentUuid":"3c6d85be-39b8-4a7d-a196-7982b6859a0d","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"3cfdca64-d5a0-407a-b98d-81d58c820453","agentId":"a98d53b8f2a71429f","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01KYf3FARQ678QkrRRuJjFSj","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"decentralized content network governance model aligned mission coherent brand multiple sites\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"How can you decide between centralized and decentralized content governance models?\",\"url\":\"https://www.linkedin.com/advice/3/how-can-you-decide-between-centralized-decentralized\"},{\"title\":\"Frontiers | Decentralizing governance: exploring the dynamics and challenges of digital commons and DAOs\",\"url\":\"https://www.frontiersin.org/journals/blockchain/articles/10.3389/fbloc.2025.1538227/full\"},{\"title\":\"Decentralized governance in action: A governance framework of digital responsibility in startups - ScienceDirect\",\"url\":\"https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S2666659625000034\"},{\"title\":\"Web Governance for State Agencies: Your Most Underrated Modernization Tool | Lullabot\",\"url\":\"https://www.lullabot.com/articles/web-governance-state-agencies-your-most-underrated-modernization-tool\"},{\"title\":\"AI brand governance: a system to align teams and agencies\",\"url\":\"https://www.ultrabrand.io/post/ai-brand-and-semantic-governance-managing-truth-across-teams-and-agencies\"},{\"title\":\"Governance models\",\"url\":\"https://docs.acquia.com/resources/governance-models\"},{\"title\":\"CMS governance models that work: How technical leaders can build structures that scale\",\"url\":\"https://www.brightspot.com/cms-resources/cms-insights/cms-governance-models-that-work\"},{\"title\":\"Decentralized Social Media | Business & Information Systems Engineering | Springer Nature Link\",\"url\":\"https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s12599-025-00952-4\"},{\"title\":\"Decentralized Governance Design: A Model-Based Approach - Vrije Universiteit Amsterdam\",\"url\":\"https://research.vu.nl/en/publications/decentralized-governance-design-a-model-based-approach/\"},{\"title\":\"Content Governance Models for Global Marketing Teams | School of Content - Content strategy, management and marketing\",\"url\":\"https://www.schoolofcontent.net/blog/content-governance-model-global-teams/\"}]\n\nI've completed a web search on your query about decentralized content network governance models aligned with mission and coherent brand across multiple sites. Here are the key findings:\n\n## Governance Models Overview\n\nMost organizations use a hybrid content governance model that combines elements of both centralized and decentralized approaches, where a central content team might set the overall strategy and standards while providing guidance to decentralized teams that create and manage content for their domains, audiences, and channels.\n\n## Balancing Mission Alignment and Brand Coherence\n\nTo maintain aligned mission and coherence, one must define and communicate the content vision, mission, and goals in alignment with business objectives and customer needs. The key is finding the right balance between control and autonomy, consistency and diversity, efficiency and effectiveness.\n\nFor organizations managing multiple sites, effective models typically combine role-based access control, structured workflows and decentralized ownership with central standards, which together support local flexibility while maintaining global consistency.\n\n## Decentralized Models with Strategic Alignment\n\nIn blockchain-based decentralized systems, centralized or semi-centralized governance models can also promote better strategic alignment, as the presence of curated councils and working groups enables the network to set and pursue long-term objectives more coherently.\n\n## Key Challenges\n\nCentralized content governance can ensure consistency, quality, and compliance, yet it can also limit creativity, agility, and responsiveness, while decentralized content governance can foster innovation, collaboration, and engagement, but can also create inconsistency, duplication, and confusion.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"d8ea834c-7bd5-4bd1-ae28-619c9ca44554","timestamp":"2026-03-15T14:19:03.907Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"3c6d85be-39b8-4a7d-a196-7982b6859a0d","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
{"parentUuid":"d8ea834c-7bd5-4bd1-ae28-619c9ca44554","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a98d53b8f2a71429f","type":"progress","data":{"type":"hook_progress","hookEvent":"PostToolUse","hookName":"PostToolUse:WebSearch","command":"bash \"${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/scripts/hooks/run-with-flags-shell.sh\" \"post:observe\" \"skills/continuous-learning-v2/hooks/observe.sh\" \"standard,strict\""},"parentToolUseID":"toolu_012Pa1443KGrBQjR7eBvdAGo","toolUseID":"toolu_012Pa1443KGrBQjR7eBvdAGo","timestamp":"2026-03-15T14:19:05.247Z","uuid":"aca676ee-0de8-4167-9e16-8ad9f9a16d9d","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
{"parentUuid":"29abd215-9ec9-448b-a583-9ffdb595b2d1","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"3cfdca64-d5a0-407a-b98d-81d58c820453","agentId":"a98d53b8f2a71429f","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012Pa1443KGrBQjR7eBvdAGo","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"revenue models mission-driven platforms alternatives to advertising non-extractive business models\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"The Mission Model Canvas: An Adapted Business Model Canvas For Mission-Driven Organizations\",\"url\":\"https://www.strategyzer.com/library/the-mission-model-canvas-an-adapted-business-model-canvas-for-mission-driven-organizations\"},{\"title\":\"Steve Blank The Mission Model Canvas – An Adapted Business Model Canvas for Mission-Driven Organizations\",\"url\":\"https://steveblank.com/2016/02/23/the-mission-model-canvas-an-adapted-business-model-canvas-for-mission-driven-organizations/\"},{\"title\":\"From an Extractive to a Non-Extractive Economy: Disentangling the Building Blocks of Non-Extractive Economic Practices by Kinanya Pijl :: SSRN\",\"url\":\"https://papers.ssrn.com/sol3/papers.cfm?abstract_id=4037070\"},{\"title\":\"Business models & social innovation: mission-driven versus profit-driven organisations: International Review of Applied Economics: Vol 34 , No 5 - Get Access\",\"url\":\"https://www.tandfonline.com/doi/full/10.1080/02692171.2020.1781066\"},{\"title\":\"Business models & social innovation: mission-driven versus profit-driven organisations: International Review of Applied Economics: Vol 34, No 5\",\"url\":\"https://www.tandfonline.com/doi/abs/10.1080/02692171.2020.1781066\"},{\"title\":\"Mission Model Canvas: The Adapted Business Model Canvas for Mission-Driven Organizations | Startup Grind\",\"url\":\"https://www.startupgrind.com/blog/mission-model-canvas-the-adapted-business-model-canvas-for-mission-driven-organizations/\"},{\"title\":\"Revenue Model Types in Software Business: Examples and Model\",\"url\":\"https://www.altexsoft.com/blog/revenue-model-types/\"},{\"title\":\"Revenue model - Wikipedia\",\"url\":\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Revenue_model\"},{\"title\":\"AI Business Models: Types, Revenue Streams & Examples\",\"url\":\"https://www.articsledge.com/post/ai-business-models\"},{\"title\":\"Mission Model or Business Model?. What can businesses learn from… | by Susie Braam | Medium\",\"url\":\"https://susiebraam.medium.com/mission-model-or-business-model-a9de7a92fbd3\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's what I found about revenue models for mission-driven platforms and alternatives to advertising-based non-extractive business models:\n\n## Key Approaches for Mission-Driven Organizations\n\nOrganizations can be designed for non-extractiveness by focusing on the organization's purpose, revenue model, legal structure, internal distribution of benefits, internal distribution of decision-making power, culture, and environmental and societal impacts.\n\nMission-driven organizations have undergone transformations to find new revenue streams and to better serve their beneficiaries, with these transformations characterized by searching for new ways of financing solutions to cope with societal challenges.\n\n## Alternative Revenue Models\n\nSeveral non-advertising approaches are being used:\n\n1. **Donations**: The donation-based model allows Wikipedia to remain independent and ad-free, which is an essential aspect of its identity and mission.\n\n2. **Mission-Focused Metrics**: Mission Achievement could be measured in various ways such as the number of refugees housed and fed, the number of soldiers saved from roadside bombs, or the number of cyberattacks prevented—none of which are measured in dollars and cents.\n\n3. **Hybrid Models**: As mission-driven organizations adopt profit-driven strategies and for-profit organizations adopt mission-driven strategies, they each take on new and sometimes borrowed characteristics, evolving into hybrid organizations.\n\n4. **Subscription/Freemium**: Freemium works by offering a product or service free of charge while charging a premium for advanced features, with a fully functional feature-limited version given away for free.\n\nThe research emphasizes that mission-driven organizations should focus on output-oriented models and tools that support the specificities of their business models, rather than simply adopting tools from the for-profit sector.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"4b58dcdf-e675-496b-9ddf-83fb16a5fe5b","timestamp":"2026-03-15T14:19:05.246Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"29abd215-9ec9-448b-a583-9ffdb595b2d1","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
{"parentUuid":"4b58dcdf-e675-496b-9ddf-83fb16a5fe5b","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a98d53b8f2a71429f","type":"progress","data":{"type":"hook_progress","hookEvent":"PostToolUse","hookName":"PostToolUse:WebSearch","command":"bash \"${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/scripts/hooks/run-with-flags-shell.sh\" \"post:observe\" \"skills/continuous-learning-v2/hooks/observe.sh\" \"standard,strict\""},"parentToolUseID":"toolu_01CWZSNqZs4Lb7rfngcGm8Lj","toolUseID":"toolu_01CWZSNqZs4Lb7rfngcGm8Lj","timestamp":"2026-03-15T14:19:08.708Z","uuid":"f92aea6d-58fc-4e05-bd0f-7b3e6b8317af","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
{"parentUuid":"b520693e-582d-4eef-8fe9-222af889a20a","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"3cfdca64-d5a0-407a-b98d-81d58c820453","agentId":"a98d53b8f2a71429f","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01CWZSNqZs4Lb7rfngcGm8Lj","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"multi-agent AI website builder deploy maintain autonomous content management 2026\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"How to Build Multi-Agent Systems: Complete 2026 Guide - DEV Community\",\"url\":\"https://dev.to/eira-wexford/how-to-build-multi-agent-systems-complete-2026-guide-1io6\"},{\"title\":\"The Best AI Agent Builders in 2026: A Comprehensive Guide to Autonomous Intelligence Platforms | FlowHunt\",\"url\":\"https://www.flowhunt.io/blog/best-ai-agent-builders-2026/\"},{\"title\":\"The Leading Multi-Agent Platform\",\"url\":\"https://crewai.com/\"},{\"title\":\"8 Best Multi-Agent AI Frameworks for 2026\",\"url\":\"https://www.multimodal.dev/post/best-multi-agent-ai-frameworks\"},{\"title\":\"Agentic & Autonomous AI Workflows in 2026: How AI Agents Are Transforming Creator Automation Pipelines\",\"url\":\"https://www.myaiassistant.blog/2026/02/agentic-autonomous-ai-workflows-in-2026.html\"},{\"title\":\"Top Multi-AI Agent Platforms In 2026\",\"url\":\"https://startupstash.com/top-multi-ai-agent-platforms/\"},{\"title\":\"Top 8 LLM Frameworks for Building AI Agents in 2026 | Second Talent\",\"url\":\"https://www.secondtalent.com/resources/top-llm-frameworks-for-building-ai-agents/\"},{\"title\":\"AI agent trends for 2026: 7 shifts to watch\",\"url\":\"https://www.salesmate.io/blog/future-of-ai-agents/\"},{\"title\":\"Best AI agent builder for 2026 | WBS CODING SCHOOL\",\"url\":\"https://www.wbscodingschool.com/blog/best-ai-agent-builder/\"},{\"title\":\"How AI Agents Are Transforming Content Ops in 2026\",\"url\":\"https://www.averi.ai/how-to/ai-agent-marketing-how-autonomous-ai-is-changing-content-ops-in-2026\"}]\n\nI've performed the web search on multi-agent AI website builders and autonomous content management in 2026. Here are the key findings:\n\n## Overview of Multi-Agent AI Systems in 2026\n\n2026 is expected to be the year of multi-agent systems, with significant enterprise adoption occurring. A multi-agent system consists of autonomous AI agents that interact within a shared environment, with each agent specializing in a specific domain like data analysis, content generation, or API integration.\n\n## Deployment and Maintenance\n\n3-7 agents work best for most workflows, and above seven, coordination complexity outweighs benefits unless you use hierarchical structures with team leaders managing subgroups.\n\nWith visual builders, templates, and preconfigured components, teams can deploy agents in hours, not months. On most platforms, building an agent takes just 15 to 60 minutes.\n\n## Autonomous Content Management\n\nFor content operations specifically, an agentic AI workflow is a goal-driven automation system where artificial intelligence acts as an autonomous agent that plans, executes multi-step tasks, evaluates outcomes, and continuously improves performance. These systems combine reasoning, memory, and tool usage to complete complex objectives with minimal human intervention.\n\nAutonomous AI workflows can operate independently for many tasks, especially repetitive and data-driven processes like content generation, SEO optimization, analytics tracking, and scheduling.\n\n## Leading Platforms\n\nFlowHunt has emerged as the leading AI agent building platform in 2026, combining powerful no-code capabilities with enterprise-grade features, standing out for its intuitive visual workflow builder, comprehensive AI model integration, and seamless deployment across multiple channels.\n\nCrewAI enables building a crew of AI agents that autonomously interact with enterprise applications and use tools to automate workflows and tasks, with or without writing code.\n\n## Market Growth and ROI\n\nThe agentic AI market will exceed $10.9B in 2026, growing at 45%+ CAGR. A typical enterprise deploying AI agents across customer support, content creation, and data analysis workflows can expect to reduce manual labor by 40-60% while simultaneously improving output quality and consistency.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"41b3b906-df10-4f62-bd72-50579b294407","timestamp":"2026-03-15T14:19:08.708Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"b520693e-582d-4eef-8fe9-222af889a20a","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
