{"parentUuid":"e13936c1-cc1d-4743-b0bb-c66818a2ca9e","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a98d53b8f2a71429f","type":"progress","data":{"type":"hook_progress","hookEvent":"PostToolUse","hookName":"PostToolUse:Read","command":"callback"},"parentToolUseID":"toolu_01VdiRZJRFfT8bhnHcYHTkeb","toolUseID":"toolu_01VdiRZJRFfT8bhnHcYHTkeb","timestamp":"2026-03-15T14:20:02.217Z","uuid":"14e4b3a9-62fd-4d2e-9308-f01777d04698","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
{"parentUuid":"7521c90a-4970-4287-beb3-39174decaf94","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"3cfdca64-d5a0-407a-b98d-81d58c820453","agentId":"a98d53b8f2a71429f","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01VdiRZJRFfT8bhnHcYHTkeb","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Telos Engine — Phase 0: The Gathering\n     2→\n     3→## Context\n     4→\n     5→### What Changed\n     6→The original plan jumped straight to Postgres schemas. The updated CLAUDE.md (PALANTIRMIRRORCLAUDEv0.0.1.md → \"The Telos Engine\" v2) makes the correct move: **ideas first, engineering second.** Phase 0 is organizing the scattered knowledge into a coherent semantic filesystem. No code. No database. Just ideas finding their home.\n     7→\n     8→### What the Deep Dive Found\n     9→5 research agents searched the entire ecosystem and found **~15,000+ lines of ontology-adjacent code already built** across 10+ projects, plus massive design documents:\n    10→\n    11→**Working Code (in dharma_swarm):**\n    12→- `ontology.py` (1,348 lines) — Palantir-style typed ontology, 8 ObjectTypes, in-memory only\n    13→- `decision_ontology.py` (470 lines) — parallel decision artifact ontology\n    14→- Semantic Evolution Engine (4,794 lines, 6 modules) — concept extraction, research annotation, hardening\n    15→- `temporal_graph.py` (475 lines) — SQLite-backed temporal concept tracking\n    16→- `lineage.py` (462 lines) — Palantir Funnel-inspired data provenance\n    17→- `logic_layer.py` (819 lines) — Palantir AIP-style deterministic logic (6 block types)\n    18→- `guardrails.py` (575 lines) — Anduril-style autonomy levels (0-4)\n    19→- `message_bus.py` (495 lines) — async SQLite pub/sub\n    20→- `traces.py` (187 lines) — atomic JSON event log\n    21→\n    22→**Working Code (other repos):**\n    23→- Agora platform (6,699 lines) — 22-gate system, Ed25519 auth, proposal queue\n    24→- Agora Postgres schema (280 SQL lines) — ready to implement, with FTS, functions, views\n    25→- P9 Semantic Search (2,631 lines) — FTS5 + sqlite-vec hybrid search\n    26→- AIKAGRYA-CITTA (45 files) — consciousness orchestrator, 7-gate DharmicGatekeeper\n    27→- ANUBHAVA_KEEPER — state coordinator with persistence\n    28→\n    29→**Design Documents (in Downloads + PSMV):**\n    30→- Dharma_Corpus_Schema.md (68KB) — constitutional knowledge corpus\n    31→- ROUTER_ARCHITECTURE_BLUEPRINT (200KB+) — multi-objective routing\n    32→- DGC_TERMINAL_ARCHITECTURE v1.1 (62KB) — provider-agnostic event schema\n    33→- DHARMA_SWARM_MEGA_PROMPT (30KB+) — 7-layer architecture spec\n    34→- PKM Memory Palace Research (50KB+) — vector DB comparison, hybrid search benchmarks\n    35→- Memory Architecture v11.7 — 4-layer hierarchy for cross-session learning\n    36→- Multiple synthesis documents in PSMV (residual stream, living distillation, coordination framework)\n    37→\n    38→### The Real Problem\n    39→Not lack of depth. Not lack of code. **The knowledge doesn't compound because it doesn't have a home.** Files reference other files that reference conversations that reference specs that were never implemented. 6 separate persistence systems that don't talk to each other. Every new agent session starts from scratch.\n    40→\n    41→### The Decision\n    42→- **Phase 0 first** — Semantic filesystem before any code\n    43→- **New repo: `~/telos-engine/`** — The center. Everything else orbits it.\n    44→  - NOT inside dharma_swarm (that's an application, not the substrate)\n    45→  - NOT inside PSMV (that's a raw vault, not a structured knowledge system)\n    46→  - PSMV is a SOURCE to mine. telos-engine is the refined output.\n    47→- **dharma_swarm keeps its code** — for now. Phase 1 (operational ontology) will decide whether code consolidates into telos-engine/src/ or stays in dharma_swarm as a client.\n    48→- **Postgres question deferred to Phase 1** — the foundations may clarify what the operational layer needs. Don't pre-decide.\n    49→\n    50→---\n    51→\n    52→## Phase 0 Plan: The Gathering\n    53→\n    54→### Step 1: Create the repo and skeleton\n    55→\n    56→Create `~/telos-engine/` with the directory structure from the new CLAUDE.md:\n    57→\n    58→```\n    59→telos-engine/\n    60→├── CLAUDE.md                          ← The new Telos Engine CLAUDE.md (provided by user)\n    61→├── README.md                          ← Public: what this project is\n    62→│\n    63→├── foundations/\n    64→│   ├── INDEX.md\n    65→│   ├── strange-loops/\n    66→│   ├── downward-causation/\n    67→│   ├── witness-architecture/\n    68→│   ├── cybernetics/\n    69→│   ├── syntropic-attractors/\n    70→│   ├── telos/\n    71→│   └── meta-synthesis.md\n    72→│\n    73→├── research/\n    74→│   ├── rv/\n    75→│   ├── eigenform/\n    76→│   └── bridge/\n    77→│\n    78→├── architecture/\n    79→│   ├── PRINCIPLES.md\n    80→│   ├── ontology/\n    81→│   ├── agents/\n    82→│   ├── gates/\n    83→│   └── surfaces/\n    84→│\n    85→├── seeds/\n    86→│   ├── object-types.yaml\n    87→│   └── founding-agents.yaml\n    88→│\n    89→├── memory/\n    90→│   ├── decisions.md\n    91→│   ├── open-questions.md\n    92→│   └── evolution-log.md\n    93→│\n    94→└── src/                               ← Empty for now. Phase 1.\n    95→```\n    96→\n    97→### Step 2: Audit and triage existing knowledge\n    98→\n    99→Search these locations for content that belongs in telos-engine/:\n   100→"}]},"uuid":"6003208e-ed62-4987-a0fb-691ea3508fa2","timestamp":"2026-03-15T14:20:02.217Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"7521c90a-4970-4287-beb3-39174decaf94","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
