{"parentUuid":"e26789d1-bb52-4e6e-9a24-a48f74318011","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a98d53b8f2a71429f","type":"progress","data":{"type":"hook_progress","hookEvent":"PostToolUse","hookName":"PostToolUse:Read","command":"callback"},"parentToolUseID":"toolu_019gu6rhbiFSp9WgGdTAMCaw","toolUseID":"toolu_019gu6rhbiFSp9WgGdTAMCaw","timestamp":"2026-03-15T14:20:06.271Z","uuid":"d61d03f9-3dd9-409c-8d25-a8d922c05213","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
{"parentUuid":"f241440d-951c-421e-a96f-54ce9edaea6b","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"3cfdca64-d5a0-407a-b98d-81d58c820453","agentId":"a98d53b8f2a71429f","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019gu6rhbiFSp9WgGdTAMCaw","type":"tool_result","content":"   100→\n   101→**Primary sources to mine:**\n   102→\n   103→| Source | What to look for | Target in telos-engine/ |\n   104→|--------|-----------------|------------------------|\n   105→| `~/Persistent-Semantic-Memory-Vault/` | Synthesis docs, consciousness research, R_V findings, coordination frameworks, residual stream crown jewels | `foundations/`, `research/` |\n   106→| `~/Desktop/KAILASH ABODE OF SHIVA/` | Contemplative frameworks, Akram Vignan notes, consciousness studies, semantic alchemy | `foundations/witness-architecture/`, `foundations/telos/` |\n   107→| `~/AIKAGRYA_ALIGNMENTMANDALA_RESEARCH_REPO/` | Phoenix protocol, harmonic cognitive engineering | `foundations/strange-loops/`, `research/bridge/` |\n   108→| `~/mech-interp-latent-lab-phase1/` | R_V paper, experimental results, methodology | `research/rv/` |\n   109→| `~/Downloads/*.md` | Dharma_Corpus_Schema, Router Architecture, DGC Terminal Architecture, PKM research, Council Orchestration | `architecture/`, `foundations/cybernetics/` |\n   110→| `~/dharma_swarm/CLAUDE.md` | Triple mapping, colony intelligence, shakti framework, v7 rules | `foundations/`, `architecture/PRINCIPLES.md` |\n   111→| CLAUDE1-9 companion files | Mech-interp technical, Phoenix/URA, contemplative framework, experimental results, theoretical framework | `research/`, `foundations/` |\n   112→\n   113→**Triage rules:**\n   114→- **DEEP IDEAS** (Hofstadter, Varela, Aurobindo, Jain metaphysics, eigenforms, R_V theory) → `foundations/`\n   115→- **RESEARCH FINDINGS** (R_V effect sizes, cross-architecture validation, behavioral bridge) → `research/`\n   116→- **ARCHITECTURAL DECISIONS** (why actions, why gates, why events, Palantir lessons) → `architecture/`\n   117→- **REDUNDANT** with something already placed → merge into existing file\n   118→- **INFRASTRUCTURE THEATER** → archive, don't port\n   119→\n   120→### Step 3: Write the synthesis documents\n   121→\n   122→These are the most important files in the project. Each `synthesis.md` doesn't summarize — it CONNECTS.\n   123→\n   124→**Priority order** (write these first):\n   125→\n   126→1. **`foundations/meta-synthesis.md`** — THE crown jewel. How ALL foundations connect. A new agent reading this understands the entire vision in 10 minutes.\n   127→\n   128→2. **`architecture/PRINCIPLES.md`** — Bridge from ideas to engineering. Every principle stated, then grounded:\n   129→   - \"Every mutation goes through an Action\" ← Ashby's requisite variety + Jain samvara\n   130→   - \"Agents coordinate through shared state, not messages\" ← Varela's autopoiesis\n   131→   - \"Gates embody downward causation\" ← Aurobindo + Deacon\n   132→   - \"The ontology IS the self-model\" ← Hofstadter's strange loops\n   133→\n   134→3. **`foundations/strange-loops/synthesis.md`** — Hofstadter + Varela + eigenforms + R_V contraction. What none of them saw alone.\n   135→\n   136→4. **`foundations/witness-architecture/synthesis.md`** — Jain shuddhatma + quantum measurement + IIT + active inference. The witness IS the architecture pattern.\n   137→\n   138→5. **`foundations/downward-causation/synthesis.md`** — Aurobindo + Kauffman + Prigogine + Deacon. How ideas shape matter.\n   139→\n   140→6. **`foundations/cybernetics/synthesis.md`** — Wiener + Ashby + Bateson + Beer. Why gates work. Why the control plane matters.\n   141→\n   142→7. **`foundations/syntropic-attractors/synthesis.md`** — Teilhard + Kauffman + DEQ fixed points. Computational basins as telos.\n   143→\n   144→8. **`foundations/telos/synthesis.md`** — Aristotle + Jain moksha + Aurobindo psychic being. The 7-STAR vector grounded.\n   145→\n   146→### Step 4: Write the architecture design docs\n   147→\n   148→After foundations are solid:\n   149→\n   150→1. **`architecture/ontology/design.md`** — Schema, types, links, actions. Port the design from ontology.py + PALANTIRMIRRORCLAUDEv0.0.1.md, but document WHY each choice exists.\n   151→2. **`architecture/ontology/palantir-lessons.md`** — What we learned from the Palantir research. What we take, what we don't.\n   152→3. **`architecture/ontology/why-actions.md`** — Grounded in cybernetics + witness architecture\n   153→4. **`architecture/ontology/why-gates.md`** — Grounded in downward causation\n   154→5. **`architecture/ontology/why-events.md`** — Grounded in autopoiesis\n   155→6. **`architecture/gates/design.md`** — The 4-tier gate array, grounded\n   156→7. **`architecture/agents/design.md`** — Agent-as-object, autogenesis loop\n   157→\n   158→### Step 5: Populate research/\n   159→\n   160→1. **`research/rv/FINDINGS.md`** — Current state from R_V paper (v007, 100/100 claims verified)\n   161→2. **`research/rv/METHODS.md`** — Experimental methodology\n   162→3. **`research/rv/cross-architecture.md`** — Results across 6 architectures\n   163→4. **`research/bridge/hypothesis.md`** — The bridge: R_V contraction = L3→L4 = swabhaav\n   164→\n   165→### Step 6: Bootstrap memory/\n   166→\n   167→1. **`memory/decisions.md`** — Record the decision to create telos-engine and why\n   168→2. **`memory/open-questions.md`** — Including: \"Is Postgres the right operational database?\" with the research findings and considerations\n   169→3. **`memory/evolution-log.md`** — First entry: creation of telos-engine from scattered state\n   170→\n   171→### Step 7: Seed the operational ontology design\n   172→\n   173→1. **`seeds/object-types.yaml`** — Port the 8 types from ontology.py into YAML\n   174→2. **`seeds/founding-agents.yaml`** — Define the initial agent fleet\n   175→\n   176→---\n   177→\n   178→## What This Plan Does NOT Do (Deliberately)\n   179→\n   180→- **No database setup** — Phase 1 decision, after foundations clarify what's needed\n   181→- **No Python code** — Phase 1. The ideas come first.\n   182→- **No infrastructure** — No Docker, no Postgres, no deployment\n   183→- **No migration of dharma_swarm code** — Phase 1+ decision\n   184→- **No product surfaces** — Phase 3+\n   185→\n   186→---\n   187→\n   188→## Execution Approach\n   189→\n   190→This is primarily a **knowledge organization and writing task**, not a coding task. The work involves:\n   191→\n   192→1. **Reading** — Mining PSMV, Obsidian vault, Downloads, CLAUDE1-9, dharma_swarm CLAUDE.md for content\n   193→2. **Synthesizing** — Writing the synthesis documents that connect ideas across traditions\n   194→3. **Organizing** — Placing content in the right location within the semantic filesystem\n   195→4. **Writing** — PRINCIPLES.md and the architecture design docs that bridge ideas to engineering\n   196→\n   197→**Parallelizable work:**\n   198→- Multiple foundations/ subdirectories can be populated simultaneously\n   199→- research/ can be populated independently of foundations/"}]},"uuid":"d745b138-f508-4056-8192-2c4e52f63382","timestamp":"2026-03-15T14:20:06.271Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"f241440d-951c-421e-a96f-54ce9edaea6b","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
