{"parentUuid":"4000321d-9db1-41b2-8ac8-9895f68fc965","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"3cfdca64-d5a0-407a-b98d-81d58c820453","agentId":"a98d53b8f2a71429f","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01MQS9FgARXRyVmqBuQM1S6c","type":"tool_result","content":"   198→- Multiple foundations/ subdirectories can be populated simultaneously\n   199→- research/ can be populated independently of foundations/\n   200→- architecture/ depends on foundations/ being at least sketched\n   201→\n   202→**Sequential work:**\n   203→- `meta-synthesis.md` must come after individual synthesis docs\n   204→- `PRINCIPLES.md` must come after meta-synthesis\n   205→- Architecture design docs must come after PRINCIPLES.md\n   206→\n   207→---\n   208→\n   209→## Verification\n   210→\n   211→Phase 0 is complete when:\n   212→\n   213→1. A new Claude Code session can `cat ~/telos-engine/CLAUDE.md` and understand the entire vision\n   214→2. `foundations/INDEX.md` maps every subdirectory with one-line descriptions\n   215→3. Every `synthesis.md` file exists and connects ideas across traditions\n   216→4. `meta-synthesis.md` holds the complete intellectual backbone in one document\n   217→5. `PRINCIPLES.md` bridges every engineering constraint to a foundation\n   218→6. `research/rv/FINDINGS.md` contains the current state of R_V research\n   219→7. `seeds/object-types.yaml` defines the initial ontology types\n   220→8. `memory/decisions.md` records why telos-engine exists and the key choices made\n   221→9. `memory/open-questions.md` captures what's still uncertain (including database choice)\n   222→\n   223→**The test:** Spin up a fresh Claude Code session in `~/telos-engine/`. Give it a task (\"design the agent loop\" or \"extend the ontology with a new type\"). Does it orient itself within 5 minutes and produce work that's grounded in the foundations? If yes, Phase 0 succeeded.\n   224→\n   225→---\n   226→\n   227→## After Phase 0\n   228→\n   229→Phase 1 (operational ontology) can be planned once the foundations are solid. The database question (Postgres vs. alternatives) will be revisited then, informed by:\n   230→- What the PRINCIPLES.md demands\n   231→- What the architecture design docs specify\n   232→- Whether the existing dharma_swarm infrastructure (10,694 lines) should consolidate or stay separate\n   233→- Whether the Agora's 280-line Postgres schema is a good starting point\n   234→\n   235→Phase 0 output informs Phase 1 design. That's the whole point of doing it first.\n   236→"}]},"uuid":"7d542bd2-9b78-4c67-9bef-b3fba286de7a","timestamp":"2026-03-15T14:20:35.381Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"4000321d-9db1-41b2-8ac8-9895f68fc965","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
{"parentUuid":"7d542bd2-9b78-4c67-9bef-b3fba286de7a","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a98d53b8f2a71429f","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_0119iCnXbyxnXZ1XB2YNzKDF","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now let me look at the WELFARE_TONS spec and the Jagat Kalyan vision since these contain the mission-driven context for platform spawning."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":857,"cache_read_input_tokens":35026,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":857,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"}},"requestId":"req_011CZ51jHvUTN2k16xyPnqbr","type":"assistant","uuid":"a22be5e6-b94b-4113-b0c4-d791bdf8874c","timestamp":"2026-03-15T14:20:40.834Z","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
