{"parentUuid":"908dcf9a-9722-4b27-9291-3167bb7e1660","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a98d53b8f2a71429f","type":"progress","data":{"type":"hook_progress","hookEvent":"PreToolUse","hookName":"PreToolUse:Read","command":"bash \"${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/scripts/hooks/run-with-flags-shell.sh\" \"pre:observe\" \"skills/continuous-learning-v2/hooks/observe.sh\" \"standard,strict\""},"toolUseID":"toolu_015c8GEMqH9c9awWD2Z8U311","parentToolUseID":"toolu_015c8GEMqH9c9awWD2Z8U311","uuid":"e2e16508-087e-4a32-a7a0-02961259e56a","timestamp":"2026-03-15T14:20:42.057Z","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
{"parentUuid":"e2e16508-087e-4a32-a7a0-02961259e56a","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a98d53b8f2a71429f","type":"progress","data":{"type":"hook_progress","hookEvent":"PostToolUse","hookName":"PostToolUse:Read","command":"bash \"${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/scripts/hooks/run-with-flags-shell.sh\" \"post:observe\" \"skills/continuous-learning-v2/hooks/observe.sh\" \"standard,strict\""},"parentToolUseID":"toolu_015c8GEMqH9c9awWD2Z8U311","toolUseID":"toolu_015c8GEMqH9c9awWD2Z8U311","timestamp":"2026-03-15T14:20:42.060Z","uuid":"68597fde-6c2d-4e6a-8765-9dbc6d2f5ce7","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
{"parentUuid":"68597fde-6c2d-4e6a-8765-9dbc6d2f5ce7","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a98d53b8f2a71429f","type":"progress","data":{"type":"hook_progress","hookEvent":"PostToolUse","hookName":"PostToolUse:Read","command":"callback"},"parentToolUseID":"toolu_015c8GEMqH9c9awWD2Z8U311","toolUseID":"toolu_015c8GEMqH9c9awWD2Z8U311","timestamp":"2026-03-15T14:20:42.060Z","uuid":"8d537ae8-3622-42ed-9530-3a394935a71d","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
{"parentUuid":"908dcf9a-9722-4b27-9291-3167bb7e1660","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"3cfdca64-d5a0-407a-b98d-81d58c820453","agentId":"a98d53b8f2a71429f","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015c8GEMqH9c9awWD2Z8U311","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Jagat Kalyan: AI-Coordinated Ecological Restoration\n     2→\n     3→## The Problem Is Circular. The Solution Should Be Too.\n     4→\n     5→AI is simultaneously displacing 85 million jobs globally and emitting 32.6-79.7 million tonnes of CO2 annually. Meanwhile, the companies building these systems are making carbon pledges they have no infrastructure to fulfill --- and the voluntary carbon market they'd buy into is plagued by phantom credits and zero social accountability.\n     6→\n     7→Three crises. One loop.\n     8→\n     9→## What Jagat Kalyan Does\n    10→\n    11→We build the coordination layer that turns AI's externalities into a self-sustaining restoration engine.\n    12→\n    13→**Side A --- Carbon Bridge**\n    14→- Per-inference carbon attribution: every API call carries its ecological cost\n    15→- Curated portfolio of verified restoration projects (reforestation, mangrove, soil carbon)\n    16→- AI-powered matching between corporate offset demand and highest-impact projects\n    17→- Three-tier verification: satellite imagery + community ground-truth + transparent ledger\n    18→\n    19→**Side B --- Grassroots**\n    20→- AI-displaced workers trained and employed in ecological restoration\n    21→- 1.5x minimum wage floor, non-negotiable\n    22→- Community consent protocol before any project begins\n    23→- Cooperative profit-sharing: communities own their restoration outcomes\n    24→\n    25→**The Loop**: AI companies fund offsets. Offsets fund restoration. Restoration employs displaced workers. Workers use AI tools to scale impact. Verified impact attracts more funding. The loop tightens.\n    26→\n    27→## The Metric: Welfare-Tons\n    28→\n    29→Standard carbon offsets count CO2. We count **welfare-tons**: CO2 sequestered multiplied by a social welfare multiplier (livelihoods created, community consent achieved, local ownership percentage). One welfare-ton prices at 5-10x a standard offset --- because it actually accounts for what matters.\n    30→\n    31→## Why This Is Different\n    32→\n    33→**Not a carbon marketplace.** Marketplaces optimize price. We optimize welfare. The matching algorithm weighs community benefit and ecological integrity, not just cost-per-ton.\n    34→\n    35→**Not a jobs program.** Jobs programs depend on grants. This is self-sustaining: corporate demand for credible offsets funds the work that generates credible offsets.\n    36→\n    37→**Not philanthropy.** The economics close. AI companies need offsets they can defend publicly. Current options are embarrassing. We give them offsets worth defending.\n    38→\n    39→**Rooted in something older.** The Jain principle *Parasparopagraho Jivanam* --- all life bound in mutual support --- is not decoration. It is the system architecture. Every node strengthens every other node. Extraction is structurally impossible because the loop only works when value circulates.\n    40→\n    41→## Where We Are\n    42→\n    43→MVP is a 4-week build: FastAPI backend, SQLite, Claude API for matching intelligence. Three pilot restoration sites identified. First corporate partners in conversation.\n    44→\n    45→Voluntary carbon market projected at $50B+ by 2030. We do not need to capture the market. We need to prove that welfare-tons command a premium --- then the market restructures around us.\n    46→\n    47→## The Ask\n    48→\n    49→We are seeking $150K in seed funding to build the MVP, run three pilot sites, and publish the welfare-ton methodology. Partners who understand that ecological restoration and displaced-worker employment are not separate problems --- they are the same problem, and the solution is a loop.\n    50→\n    51→---\n    52→\n    53→*Jagat Kalyan* means \"universal welfare\" in Sanskrit. It is not a brand name. It is a design constraint.\n    54→"}]},"uuid":"dde9d5c0-46f6-4116-af4b-7cf6a00f02ad","timestamp":"2026-03-15T14:20:42.060Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"908dcf9a-9722-4b27-9291-3167bb7e1660","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
